# =============================================================================
# DevOps Toolbox — Docker Build Context Exclusions
# =============================================================================
# Files and directories listed here are excluded from the build context sent
# to the Docker daemon. This keeps builds fast and prevents unnecessary or
# sensitive files from being accidentally copied into the image.
#
# Note: The Dockerfile uses explicit COPY instructions for everything it needs
# from the dependencies/ directory, so only those files enter the image.
# This file primarily protects against accidental inclusion of editor
# artifacts, secrets, and local tooling state.
# =============================================================================

# --- Version control ---------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore

# --- GitHub Actions ----------------------------------------------------------
# The pipeline definition has no role inside the image itself
.github

# --- Dev container config ----------------------------------------------------
# The .devcontainer folder is for VS Code tooling, not the image build
.devcontainer

# --- Local environment and secrets -------------------------------------------
# .env is gitignored but double-listed here as a safety net
.env
*.env

# --- Editor and OS artifacts -------------------------------------------------
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Documentation -----------------------------------------------------------
README.md
CHANGELOG.md
LICENSE
